SIMPLE: divisive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Divisive
<hw>Di*vi"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>divisif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Indicating division or
distribution.</def> <rj><au>Mede.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Creating, or tending to create, division,
separation, or difference.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It [culture] is after all a dainty and <qex>divisive</qex>
quality, and can not reach to the depths of humanity.</q> <rj><qau>J. C.
Shairp.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Di*vi"sive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Di*vi"sive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>
<rj><au>Carlyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Divisor</ent>⟦br⟧
